      "id": "note--analysis-summary",
      "created": "2026-04-03T03:00:00.000Z",
      "modified": "2026-04-03T03:00:00.000Z",
      "content": "The embedded JWT token in the obfuscated JS payload exposed the operator alias 'Smokest', a platform-assigned userId, and the build configuration. This indicates a multi-tenant MaaS platform where Smokest is a customer. The Deno runtime approach achieves 0/57 AV detection, representing a significant evasion technique. The hosting on Dedik Services (AS207043), a known BPH provider, and registration via CNOBIN (Hong Kong registrar) are consistent with cybercrime infrastructure patterns.",
      "object_refs": ["campaign--clicksmoke-2026"]
    }
